Two suspects caught with the fresh head of a young boy and a pair of hands have told police in Kwara State that the human parts were meant for alfa, a religious scholar, based in Ilorin. The suspects, Wasiu Omonose, male, aged 35yrs, of Abioye compound, Share and, Akanbi Ibrahim ‘M’ aged 32yrs of Sayo street, Share, confessed that the human parts were meant for ritual purposes. According to the police report, police patrol on Sunday, around 11 am intercepted two men on a motorcycle. The suspect attempted to evade the officers on stop and search duty, which aroused the suspicion of the police operatives. The suspects were then given a hot chase and forced to a stop. In the process of searching them, a bag containing a fresh human head and hands were found in their possession. “For the umpteenth time, the commissioner of police Kwara State, Cp Tuesday Assayomo psc (+) is warning criminal elements to relocate from Kwara State, as the Police Command would not fold its arms and allow criminals of whatever nomenclature truncate the peace and harmony presently existing in Kwara State,” the police statement signed by SP Ajayi Okasanmi spokesman for the state police command. However, The police while making a statement on the arrest were quiet over whether they would bring the alfa in for questioning.